# Code Structure and File Size

## Core Principle
- Prefer clean, modular structure over quick monolithic edits.

## Organization
- If a file starts becoming too large or mixed-responsibility, split logic into focused modules.
- Create new packages/folders/components when it improves clarity and ownership.
- Keep UI components small and composable; extract reusable pieces early.
- Keep backend services focused; move unrelated logic into dedicated service/helper modules.

## File Length Guidance
- Avoid adding substantial logic to already long files.
- Prefer extracting new functions/classes/hooks/components rather than extending large files.
- Keep each file scoped to a single primary concern.

## While Implementing Changes
- Preserve existing behavior while refactoring for structure.
- Favor incremental extraction over risky large rewrites.
- Keep imports and module boundaries clean and explicit.
